<head>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="/resources/css/style.css">
	<script src="/scripts/global.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
	<h2 onclick="redirectToRoot()"><span class="green">spotify</span> toolbox â€¢ find playlist genre</h2>

	<form action="/playlist-genre" method="get">
		<input type="text" name="link" placeholder="paste spotify playlist link" class="input-text-style" value="">
		<!-- debug value: https://open.spotify.com/playlist/2mbDaBZ0mpaQ5alXDDYzeE?si=13b01195f439436d -->
		<input type="submit" onclick="displayWaitingSection()" class="input-submit-style" value="analyze">

	</form>

	<hr>

	<div id="waiting-section" style="display: none;">
		<div class="dot-windmill"></div>
		<p> analyzing.. </p>
		<p> this might take up to 30 sec </p>
	</div>

	<div id="page-content">
		<h3> how it works? </h3>
		<p> 1) copy spotify playlist link </p>
		<IMG SRC="https://i.imgur.com/qyY8xR4.gif" class="how-it-works-resource" style="width: 847px; height: 631px">
		<p> 2) paste it and click 'analyze' </p>
		<IMG SRC="https://i.imgur.com/XqQUuMo.gif" class="how-it-works-resource" style="width: 1142px; height: 137px">
		<p> 3) wait for the analysis to finish </p>
		<IMG SRC="https://i.imgur.com/UnSukGJ.gif" class="how-it-works-resource" style="width: 425px; height: 162px">
		<p> 4) check analysis result </p>
		<IMG SRC="https://i.imgur.com/JBV1uiX.png" class="how-it-works-resource" style="width: 422px; height: 694px">
		<p> <span class="green"><b>70</b><span class="percentage">%</span></span> this means that 70% of the tracks* in
			this playlist are classified by Spotify as a certain genre of music </p>
		<p> some tracks are <span style="color: red">not classified</span>, it's indicated at the botom of analysis
			results</p>
		<p> --- </p>
		<p class="side-note"><em> * actually Spotify classifies artists rather than tracks, so to be precise 70% means
				that
				70% of the tracks
				in this playlist were created by artists related to the genre </em></p>
	</div>

</body>